You&#39;d probably have to use `componentDidUpdate` lifecycle method. So given that `userVisit` is dependent on the result of `targetArticle`  and assuming you are looking to this.props. for the updated Redux state, something like this should get you there:

``` lang javascript
componentDidUpdate(prevProps) {
  if(prevProps.article !== this.props.article) {
    // Now you have access to targetArticle&#39;s result and updated Redux state
    userVisit(match.params.slug, this.props.article.title)
  }
}
```

More in the docs: https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#componentdidupdate

